WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:17.140
 

00:00:17.140 --> 00:00:17.870
Hello.

00:00:17.870 --> 00:00:19.170
I'm Terry Fisher.

00:00:19.170 --> 00:00:23.040
This is the fifth of 12
lectures on copyright.

00:00:23.040 --> 00:00:25.730
Our topic today is authorship.

00:00:25.730 --> 00:00:28.300
We'll be examining the
rules that determine

00:00:28.300 --> 00:00:32.860
what person or organization owns the
copyright in a particular copyrighted

00:00:32.860 --> 00:00:33.910
work.

00:00:33.910 --> 00:00:36.870
How those rules have evolved over time.

00:00:36.870 --> 00:00:39.560
And whether they make sense.

00:00:39.560 --> 00:00:43.190
As usual, I'll be concentrating
on the law in the United States,

00:00:43.190 --> 00:00:46.910
but will also mention some issues
on which the law in other countries

00:00:46.910 --> 00:00:50.570
diverges from that in the US.

00:00:50.570 --> 00:00:53.030
Also, as usual, I'll be
illustrating the lecture

00:00:53.030 --> 00:00:55.520
with various audiovisual materials.

00:00:55.520 --> 00:00:57.810
So it would be best if
you watch the lecture

00:00:57.810 --> 00:01:01.750
on a device with a good sized screen.

00:01:01.750 --> 00:01:04.160
One of those illustrative
materials will be

00:01:04.160 --> 00:01:10.400
a map prepared using the MindManager
